## i18n discipline

- Every user-visible string must come from `useAppTranslation()` (`@/shared/i18n/useAppTranslation`).
- Locale resources live in `shared/i18n/resources/{en,fr,ar}.json`. Adding a key to one file is incomplete — add it to all three.
- Use namespaced keys (`feature.subarea.thing`), not flat strings.
- Run `pnpm i18n:check` before opening a PR. CI must fail when keys diverge across `en` / `fr` / `ar`.
- For Arabic, `applyRtlIfNeeded(lang)` flips RTL. Do not assume `flexDirection: 'row'` or absolute `left/right` positions — use `start`/`end` and the `I18nManager` API.
- Date / number formatting goes through `Intl.*`, not hand-rolled string concatenation.

## RTK Query conventions

- One shared API instance lives at `shared/api/api.ts`. Feature endpoints attach via `api.injectEndpoints({ endpoints, overrideExisting: false })`.
- New endpoints must:
  - declare a `tagTypes` value in `shared/api/api.ts` (add it once at the top).
  - `provideTags` on read endpoints with `{ type, id }` granularity, not just `[type]`.
  - `invalidatesTags` on write endpoints with the precise ids touched.
  - set `keepUnusedDataFor` deliberately when caching matters (default 60s; use higher for catalogs, lower for personalized data).
- Use `queryFn` (not `query`) for Supabase calls. Wrap the Supabase call and map errors to `ApiError`.
- Never call `supabase.from(...)` directly inside a screen or presentational component. Go through an endpoint or a hook that owns the endpoint.

## Accessibility minimums

- Touch targets ≥ 44pt. Use `IconButton` or wrap small icons in a sized `Pressable`.
- Color contrast: text against `theme.colors.bg` must hit WCAG AA (≥ 4.5:1 for body, ≥ 3:1 for large).
- Every interactive element needs `accessibilityRole` + `accessibilityLabel` (translated). Decorative-only icons get `accessibilityElementsHidden` / `importantForAccessibility="no"`.
- Forms use `accessibilityHint` for non-obvious behavior. Errors are announced (not just visual).
- Animations must not be the only signal. Pair motion with text or icon state.
- Honor `Reduce Motion` preference: gate non-essential animations on `useReducedMotion()` (Reanimated).

## Theme

- Read colors / spacing / radii / typography only from `useTheme()`. No hex literals in feature code.
- Status bar is `light`. The app is dark-only. If you find yourself adding `userInterfaceStyle === 'light'` branching, stop and ask.

## After changes

Update the relevant feature doc and `/docs/decisions/changelog.md` in the same change.
